⚠️ Your interpretation of TaskStatus

You wrote:

which is converting raw numbers.

This is the one misconception.

It isn't converting numbers.

It is converting strings into Enum objects.

Look at your Enum carefully:

class TaskStatus(Enum):
    TODO = "todo"
    IN_PROGRESS = "in_progress"
    REVIEW = "review"
    DONE = "done"

Notice the values.

They are strings.

Not numbers.

Then later:

status = TaskStatus(status_filter)

Suppose

status_filter = "done"

Python does this:

TaskStatus("done")

↓

TaskStatus.DONE

Likewise

"in_progress"

↓

TaskStatus.IN_PROGRESS

It converts a plain string into the proper enum member.

The opposite would be:

TaskStatus.DONE.value

which gives

"done"

So think of it like this:

String

↓

Enum

↓

Business Logic

rather than

Number

↓

Enum

Numbers are only used in TaskPriority.

